5: Me?! Of all people, why me?!
9:
Kids and the holidays... Two things I
have very little patience for.
18:
E-every year we have an event
where an adventurer dresses up like
Santa Claus and passes out
presents to the kids...
22:
And this year there were a couple of
people who suggested having
Bianca play the role of Santa!
31:
My thoughts exactly. See how
absurd this is?
35:
Somebody in the Guild is out to get
me, and you're going to tell me who
it is! Spill it, Lilie!
40:
Nobody's out to get you! Erm, well,
knowing you, I actually can't
guarantee that... But I have a good
reason for picking you—just hear me
out!
42:
This may come as a surprise to you,
but it seems like you've got quite a
number of fans among the kids!
46:
...Lilie, my dear, are you sure you're
not confusing me with someone
else?
50:
This job... Does Bianca really have to
go through with it?
54:
We can't force her to do anything, of
course! But all those little kids are
really looking forward to seeing her!
It'd be a shame to let them down.
61:
Come, my little dearies! Your master
has arrived bearing gifts for
all—naughty and nice alike!
64:
If you're trying to act like Santa, I'm
not really seeing it...
69:
Quiet, you! This isn't exactly my
normal routine!
74:
Perhaps it isn't, but I must admit...
You and Aperio have wonderful
matching outfits!
84:
*sigh* Maybe this was a bad idea
after all...
88:
Without further ado, let's get this
show on the road! Santa's in
town—and she's got plenty of
presents to give out!
94:
Hehehe. Are you interested in
becoming my little pet? Just say the
magic words and I'll give you some
TLC!
99:
S-sorry about that! It looks like we
mistook you for someone else!
102:
Whoops! Looks like an honest
mistake...
106:
Th-that's right! People make
mistakes all the time!
113:
I don't need your sympathies. Like I
said before, I'm not cut out for—
119:
Huh? This event is for children only,
sir...
122:
Apologies m'lady! But I couldn't wait
another second longer to see you!
Please, punish this pathetic fool as
you see fit!
126:
...And why should I waste my
precious time on a buffoon like you?
129:
Ahh, yes! Just like that! Thank you so
much!
132:
I hope he got what he wanted.
Adults need presents from time to
time as well, I suppose.
136:
Th-that was supposed to be a
present?!
142:
Hmm? It looks like more children are
headed this way!
147:
H-happy holidays! Here for some
presents? Let's see what we've got.
150:
Miss Bianca! There's one more thing
we want!
152: That rabbit! Can he be my pet?
154:
He's a raccoon, not a rabbit,
dummy! And I already called dibs!
He's going to be MY pet!
157:
Are they imitating me? ...I might
have more influence over these
children than I thought.
160:
I'm sorry dearies, but he's actually
my pet. I'd be terribly sad to give
him up. You can understand that,
can't you?
163:
How about this... Ten years from
now, come back and talk to me
again. By then you'll be old enough
to have your own pet!
169:
...I feel like this isn't your average day
in the life of Santa Claus.
172:
It's definitely not... But hey! Those
kids looked happy, so who cares?
177:
I just hope that I don't get any
complaints from their parents...
181:
A-are you Lady Bianca?! Is Aperio
with you too?
184:
That's me. And yes, Aperio is right
over there.
193:
Oh my gosh it's the real Aperio! This
is so COOL!
196: You're a fan of his, are you?
199:
That's right! I mean, he's a dragon!
They're so awesome—I can't believe
you're friends with one!
202:
Aperio, how about showing our
friend here a trick?
213:
Happy holidays. Here's a little
something from me and Aperio.
216:
And be sure to come back once
you're a bit older. Who knows,
maybe you can even be my pet?
Hehe.
220:
That questionable last comment
aside, I would say that you've made
quite a good Santa, Bianca!
224:
Hmm? But I wasn't pretending to be
Santa just now. I was just acting as I
normally would.
226:
Giving back to one's loyal subjects is
a queen's duty, is it not?
229:
You know, the offer still stands. If you
become my pet, I'll give you
everything you could possibly want.
234:
*sigh* Just when I was trying to
compliment you...
